# Research Context

## Project Goal
Develop quantization-aware multimodal recommendation system combining:
- GPFQ (Greedy Path-Following Quantization) for weight compression
- Graph Convolutional Networks with multimodal features (visual + text + ID)
- Contrastive learning with denoising for robust representations

## Algorithm Overview
GPFQ dynamical system:
- u_t = u_{t-1} + w_t*X_t - q_t*X_t  (error accumulation)
- q_t = Q(w_t + X_t^T * u_{t-1} / ||X_t||^2)  (greedy quantization)
- Stability theorem: ||u_N||_2 decays as sqrt(log N / m) w.h.p.
- Goal: minimize ||XW - XQ||_F, not ||W - Q||_F

## Multimodal GCN Architecture
- Graph: G = (Users, Items, Edges from interactions)
- Node features: visual (CLIP-ViT-L/14), text (BERT-base), ID (learnable)
- Graph conv: H^(l+1) = sigma(D^{-1/2} A D^{-1/2} H^(l) W^(l))
- Fusion: late fusion with attention-weighted combination
- Loss: BPR + InfoNCE (temperature=0.2)

## Datasets
- Amazon Baby, Sports, Clothing (standard splits)
- Evaluation: Recall@10, NDCG@10 (top-K filtering seen items)

## Code Repository Structure
- src/models/gpfq_quantizer.py    — GPFQ core algorithm
- src/models/multimodal_gnn.py    — GCN with multimodal fusion
- src/models/contrastive.py       — InfoNCE + denoising losses
- src/data/amazon_loader.py       — Dataset loading pipeline
- src/train/trainer.py            — Training loop (PyTorch Lightning)
- src/train/evaluator.py          — Recall@K, NDCG@K metrics
